"use strict";(self.webpackChunkworking_group_two_website=self.webpackChunkworking_group_two_website||[]).push([[697],{19265:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"title":"Service Manager","subtitle":"Permanent employee, full-time - Norway - Oslo","id":"961376","jobDescriptions":["\\n                            <name>The team and your role </name>\\n                            <value>\\n\\n                                <p>Our vision is to create programmable mobile networks to allow our customers and their end-users to create more valuable and useful products and services. We do this by deploying a programmable core network, making it accessible through developer-friendly APIs, and then creating a marketplace where customers and developers can meet. On the journey there we create a consistent, cloud-based, highly efficient core network delivered as-a-service. We know where we\u2019re going, and with a lot of trust in each other, we\u2019ll pave the way there together.</p><p>We are in an exciting expansion phase and in addition to scaling up all our engineering teams we are growing our world-class&nbsp;<em>Customer Success Team</em>.</p><p>So, if you have a passion for customers and tech, this is a great opportunity to join a strong international team. We are looking for a <strong>Service Manage</strong>r&nbsp;with excellent communication and interpersonal skills, who knows how to build positive and productive working relationships with customers for business growth. You will work in a dedicated Customer Success Team consisting of Service Managers, Delivery Managers, and Technical Support Engineers.</p><p>As our <strong>Service Manager&nbsp;</strong>you will play a key role as the orchestrator of the technical relationship with the customer.</p><br><p>Who are you? We believe you:&nbsp;</p><ul><li><p>Most likely have a solid experience in a customer facing role within telecom.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>You are familiar with terms like IPSec, Sigtran, SS7, Diameter, SIP, BGP, LTE, UMTS, GSM, EPC, IMS.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>Deeply understand customer\u2019s end to end solutions and requirements.</p></li><li><p>Prioritize tasks based on customer feedback and business impact.</p></li></ul><br><p>In this role you will:&nbsp;</p><ul><li><p>Drive operational relationships, including periodic check-in calls or meetings to review overall architecture and operational health of our business with the customer.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>Be the liaison towards Engineering for the coordination of customer requested changes.</p></li><li><p>Oversee service implementation plans and timelines.</p></li><li><p>Track and report business and operational metrics for the assigned accounts.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>Lead training and technical advice to the customer, in combination with Product Management, Customer Service and Operations organizations.</p></li><li><p>Promote WGTWO service roadmap to assigned accounts to maximize value.</p></li><li><p>Act as first level escalation contact.</p></li><li><p>Act as the customers advocate into WGTWO.</p></li></ul>\\n\\n                            </value>\\n                        ","\\n                            <name>Our company culture</name>\\n                            <value>\\n\\n                                <p>What\'s it like to work at Working Group Two?</p><ul><li><p>We are a small team that values getting things done in a professional manner.</p></li><li><p>We encourage curiosity and creativity.</p></li><li><p>We aim to create a warm and welcoming work environment.</p></li><li><p>We treat our coworkers well and offer competitive benefits to employees.</p></li><li><p>We work remotely, hybrid and on-site, basically the way each prefers, and have offices in Norway (Oslo and Trondheim) and Sweden, engineering hubs in Germany and Japan, and employees in 13 countries.</p></li><li><p>To learn more about \u201cthe way we roll\u201d we suggest you have a quick read through <a href=\\"https://www.wgtwo.com/blog/were-all-grownups-here\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener\\">here.</a></p></li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>What\'s next?</strong></p>If you\'re interested in working with us, please apply though the link below, or contact Theresa (theresa@wgtwo.com) or Marietta (marietta@wgtwo.com) for any questions.\\n\\n                            </value>\\n                        "]}')}}]);